<HI>in p. 15 which we cannot but except again&s;t.</HI><Q> A Scripture, <HI>&s;ai<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">h <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e,</HI> which has re&s;pect to the times of the Go&s;pel, &s;everely rebukes tho&s;e Ministers, which &s;hall bring men that are uncircumci&s;ed in heart <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> unregenerate per&s;ons) into the &s;a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ctuary, into the Church of God, to eat the Bread and drink the Blood, which they that are there, partake o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, <HI>Ezek 44.7, 9.</HI></Q>
